ARGUMENTS

[M] indicates if the argument is mandatory on the supported platform.

-mode

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork [M]

DESCRIPTION

Action to perform. This parameter is supported using the following:

Valid options are:

create

Create -count OAM Bridges on -port_handle. Attach MIPs and MEPs to configure topology.

reset

Remove all OAM bridges from port $port_handle and OAM bridge specified with -handle parameter.

modify

NOT SUPPORTED

DEFAULT

 None

-continuity_check

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork

DESCRIPTION

Enable Continuity Check sending.

DEFAULT

 None

-continuity_check_interval

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork

DESCRIPTION

Define the interval between Continuity Check messages.

Valid options are:

Not defined

1s

(DEFAULT)

DEFAULT

1s

-count

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork

DESCRIPTION

Number of OAM Bridges to configure. A topology will be created on each bridge using parameter mip_count, mep_count, md_level and domain_level. If a bridge with Bridge Id -bridge_id already exists on port -port_handle it will be used. Otherwise a new bridge is created.

DEFAULT

1

-domain_level

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork

DESCRIPTION

If this parameter is configured to 'level0' the topology will be a Hub and Spoke topology. Ixia port will have a number of bridges equal to -count parameter. Each bridge will have -mip_count MIPs connected in series and -mep_count MEPs connected to the last MIP. If mip_count is 0, all MEPs are connected directly to the bridge.Example: -count = 1; mep_count = 2; mip_count = 1IxiaPort -- Bridge1 -- MIP1 -- MEP1\--MEP2If this parameter is configured to any other level, the topology will be a Tree topology spanning across multiple levels. The starting md level will be configured with -md_level parameter and the ending md level will be configured using -domain_level parameter.Example -count = 1; mip_count = 1; mep_count = 2; -domain_level = 1; md_level = 0IxiaPort -- Bridge1 -- MIP1 -- MEP1 -- MIP2 -- MEP2\ \-- MEP3\--MEP4 -- MIP3 -- MEP5\-- MEP6

Valid options are:

level0

(DEFAULT)

DEFAULT

level0

-encap

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork

DESCRIPTION

The ethernet encapsulation for this port.

Valid options are:

ethernet_ii

(DEFAULT)

sap

NOT SUPPORTED

DEFAULT

ethernet_ii

-fault_alarm_interval

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork

DESCRIPTION

Define the interval between alarm or lock signals.

Valid options are:

1s

(DEFAULT)

DEFAULT

1s

-fault_alarm_signal

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork

DESCRIPTION

Enable the Alarm Indication Signal (AIS) transmission with a link is disabled.

DEFAULT

 None

-handle

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork

DESCRIPTION

OAM bridge handle for -mode 'reset'.

DEFAULT

 None

-mac_local

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork

DESCRIPTION

The MAC address for the Maintenance Points. If a bridge having Bridge ID equal to the value of the -bridge_id parameter already exists on the port handle, the default mac_local value will be calculated by incrementing the mac address of the last MP from this bridge. (DEFAULT = 00de..00)

DEFAULT

 None

-mac_local_incr_mode

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork

DESCRIPTION

How to modify MP mac address from one MP to the next.

Valid options are:

none

(DEFAULT ) do not modify

increment

increment using mac_local_step

decrement

decrement using mac_local_step

list

use mac addresses specified with mac_local_list. If the number of MAC

random

generate random MAC addresses.

DEFAULT

none

-mac_local_list

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork

DESCRIPTION

Use when -mac_local_incr_mode is list. List of MAC addresses.

DEFAULT

 None

-mac_local_repeat

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork

DESCRIPTION

Use when -mac_local_incr_mode is increment or decrement. Defines the number of times to use a MAC address before incrementing/decrementing.

DEFAULT

1

-mac_local_step

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork

DESCRIPTION

Use when -mac_local_incr_mode is increment or decrement. Defines the step used to increment the MP Mac address.

DEFAULT

00:00:00:00:00:01

-md_integer

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork

DESCRIPTION

Used when -md_name_format is 'mac_addr' along with -md_mac parameter. The MD Name will be -.

DEFAULT

0

-md_level

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork

DESCRIPTION

Define the Maintenance Domain Level to be used.

DEFAULT

0

-md_mac

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork

DESCRIPTION

Used when -md_name_format is 'mac_addr' along with -md_mac parameter. The MD Name will be -.

DEFAULT

00:00:00:00:00:01

-md_name

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork

DESCRIPTION

Used when -md_name_format is 'domain_name' or 'char_str'. Define the MD Name.

DEFAULT

DEFAULT

-md_name_format

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork

DESCRIPTION

Define the format for MD Name.

Valid options are:

none

do not use MD Name.

domain_name

uses -md_name parameter to define the MD Name

mac_addr

uses -md_mac and -md_integer parameters to define the MD Name

char_str

(DEFAULT) uses -md_name parameter to define the MD Name

icc_based

valid for -oam_standard itu-t_y1731 to define the MEG Id.

DEFAULT

char_str

-md_name_length

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork

DESCRIPTION

Define the length of the MD Name.

DEFAULT

7

-mep_id_incr_mode

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork

DESCRIPTION

Configures how the MPE Id value will be modified between MEPs

Valid options are:

none

decrement

Decrement MEP Id using -mep_id_step parameter

list

random

Generate random MEP IDs.

DEFAULT

none

-return_method

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork

DESCRIPTION

keyed_list (default) - always return the traffic endpoint handles as a list using the 'traffic_handles' key, no matter how long it takeskeyed_list_or_array - when more than 2000 traffic enpoint handles need to be retrieved, the key 'traffic_handles_array' will be returned instead of traffic endpoint handles as a list using the 'traffic_handles'. This key, traffic_handles_array, represents the name of the array to be used for reading the traffic endpoint handles. This method has been introduced to increase performance when returning and reading traffic handles. Returning a huge list in the tcl console can make the console hang.array - the key traffic_handles_array will be returned instead of the traffic_handles list of traffic endpoints. This key, traffic_handles_array, represents the name of the array to be used for reading the traffic handles. values are the statistics values. This method has been introduced to increase performance when returning and reading traffic handles. Returning a huge list in the tcl console can make the console hang.

DEFAULT

 None

RETURN VALUES

Supported Platform Details

IxNetwork

status

$::SUCCESS | $::FAILURE

log

When status is failure, contains more information.

handle

The list of OAM Bridges created.

traffic_handles

List of handles that can be used as emulation_dst_handle and emulation_src_handle values in ::<namespace>::traffic_config.

traffic_handles_array

The name of the array to be used for reading the traffic endpoint handles. This key is returned when more than 2000 traffic endpoint handles need to be retrieved.

mode

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork [M]

DESCRIPTION

Action to perform. This parameter is supported using the following:

Valid options are:

create

Create -count OAM Bridges on -port_handle. Attach MIPs and MEPs to configure topology.

reset

Remove all OAM bridges from port $port_handle and OAM bridge specified with -handle parameter.

modify

NOT SUPPORTED

DEFAULT

 None

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork

DESCRIPTION

Define the interval between Continuity Check messages.

Valid options are:

Not defined

1s

(DEFAULT)

DEFAULT

1s

count

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork

DESCRIPTION

Number of OAM Bridges to configure. A topology will be created on each bridge using parameter mip_count, mep_count, md_level and domain_level. If a bridge with Bridge Id -bridge_id already exists on port -port_handle it will be used. Otherwise a new bridge is created.

DEFAULT

1

domain_level

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork

DESCRIPTION

If this parameter is configured to 'level0' the topology will be a Hub and Spoke topology. Ixia port will have a number of bridges equal to -count parameter. Each bridge will have -mip_count MIPs connected in series and -mep_count MEPs connected to the last MIP. If mip_count is 0, all MEPs are connected directly to the bridge.Example: -count = 1; mep_count = 2; mip_count = 1IxiaPort -- Bridge1 -- MIP1 -- MEP1\--MEP2If this parameter is configured to any other level, the topology will be a Tree topology spanning across multiple levels. The starting md level will be configured with -md_level parameter and the ending md level will be configured using -domain_level parameter.Example -count = 1; mip_count = 1; mep_count = 2; -domain_level = 1; md_level = 0IxiaPort -- Bridge1 -- MIP1 -- MEP1 -- MIP2 -- MEP2\ \-- MEP3\--MEP4 -- MIP3 -- MEP5\-- MEP6

Valid options are:

level0

(DEFAULT)

DEFAULT

level0

return_method

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork

DESCRIPTION

keyed_list (default) - always return the traffic endpoint handles as a list using the 'traffic_handles' key, no matter how long it takeskeyed_list_or_array - when more than 2000 traffic enpoint handles need to be retrieved, the key 'traffic_handles_array' will be returned instead of traffic endpoint handles as a list using the 'traffic_handles'. This key, traffic_handles_array, represents the name of the array to be used for reading the traffic endpoint handles. This method has been introduced to increase performance when returning and reading traffic handles. Returning a huge list in the tcl console can make the console hang.array - the key traffic_handles_array will be returned instead of the traffic_handles list of traffic endpoints. This key, traffic_handles_array, represents the name of the array to be used for reading the traffic handles. values are the statistics values. This method has been introduced to increase performance when returning and reading traffic handles. Returning a huge list in the tcl console can make the console hang.

DEFAULT

 None

IxNetwork

status

log

When status is failure, contains more information.

handle

The list of OAM Bridges created.

List of handles that can be used as emulation_dst_handle and emulation_src_handle values in ::<namespace>::traffic_config.

traffic_handles_array

The name of the array to be used for reading the traffic endpoint handles. This key is returned when more than 2000 traffic endpoint handles need to be retrieved.

count

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork

DESCRIPTION

Number of OAM Bridges to configure. A topology will be created on each bridge using parameter mip_count, mep_count, md_level and domain_level. If a bridge with Bridge Id -bridge_id already exists on port -port_handle it will be used. Otherwise a new bridge is created.

DEFAULT

1

domain_level

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork

DESCRIPTION

If this parameter is configured to 'level0' the topology will be a Hub and Spoke topology. Ixia port will have a number of bridges equal to -count parameter. Each bridge will have -mip_count MIPs connected in series and -mep_count MEPs connected to the last MIP. If mip_count is 0, all MEPs are connected directly to the bridge.Example: -count = 1; mep_count = 2; mip_count = 1IxiaPort -- Bridge1 -- MIP1 -- MEP1\--MEP2If this parameter is configured to any other level, the topology will be a Tree topology spanning across multiple levels. The starting md level will be configured with -md_level parameter and the ending md level will be configured using -domain_level parameter.Example -count = 1; mip_count = 1; mep_count = 2; -domain_level = 1; md_level = 0IxiaPort -- Bridge1 -- MIP1 -- MEP1 -- MIP2 -- MEP2\ \-- MEP3\--MEP4 -- MIP3 -- MEP5\-- MEP6

Valid options are:

level0

(DEFAULT)

DEFAULT

level0

return_method

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork

DESCRIPTION

keyed_list (default) - always return the traffic endpoint handles as a list using the 'traffic_handles' key, no matter how long it takeskeyed_list_or_array - when more than 2000 traffic enpoint handles need to be retrieved, the key 'traffic_handles_array' will be returned instead of traffic endpoint handles as a list using the 'traffic_handles'. This key, traffic_handles_array, represents the name of the array to be used for reading the traffic endpoint handles. This method has been introduced to increase performance when returning and reading traffic handles. Returning a huge list in the tcl console can make the console hang.array - the key traffic_handles_array will be returned instead of the traffic_handles list of traffic endpoints. This key, traffic_handles_array, represents the name of the array to be used for reading the traffic handles. values are the statistics values. This method has been introduced to increase performance when returning and reading traffic handles. Returning a huge list in the tcl console can make the console hang.

DEFAULT

 None

RETURN VALUES

Supported Platform Details

IxNetwork

status

$::SUCCESS | $::FAILURE

log

When status is failure, contains more information.

handle

The list of OAM Bridges created.

traffic_handles

List of handles that can be used as emulation_dst_handle and emulation_src_handle values in ::<namespace>::traffic_config.

traffic_handles_array

The name of the array to be used for reading the traffic endpoint handles. This key is returned when more than 2000 traffic endpoint handles need to be retrieved.
